  "original_title": "\u0dbd\u0ddc\u0dbb\u0dd2 - \u0db6\u0dc3\u0dca \u0d9c\u0dd0\u0da7\u0dd3 \u0d85\u0dba\u0dd9\u0d9a\u0dca \u0db8\u0dbb\u0dd4\u0da7",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Lorry-bus collided and one person died",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "A private bus traveling from Galle to Matara collided with a lorry on the Galle Sea Road this morning (30th) when it collided with another vehicle. The driver of the bus was killed. Police said.",
        "The deceased is the driver of the private bus named Miran Chanaka (33) resident of Nagoda area of \u200b\u200bGammaddagoda. The 48-year-old lorry driver and the 40-year-old lorry assistant who are residents of Horangalla Minuwangoda area were seriously injured in this accident.",
        "At the time of the accident, the bus was also in the bus and there was no accident. The lorry is a newspaper distribution lorry and the police said that the accident occurred while the lorry was driving from Mataradesa towards Galle after the distribution of newspapers.",
        "The investigation will be conducted under the direction of Mr. Kapila Senapati De Silva, Head of Galle Police Inspector."
      ],
